SIMPLE: untwist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Untwist
<hw>Un*twist"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>twist</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To separate and open, as twisted threads; to turn
back, as that which is twisted; to untwine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If one of the twines of the twist do <qex>untwist</qex>,⟦br⟧
The twine that <qex>untwisteth</qex>, <qex>untwisteth</qex> the
twist.</q> <rj><qau>Wallis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To untie; to open; to disentangle.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unty</ent>⟦br⟧
